  "body": "When you generate your second cluster, suddenly you'll find that nothing works from browsers. The ca/cert pairs we make reuse serial numbers. Firefox says:\n\n```\nYour certificate contains the same serial number as another certificate issued by the certificate authority.\n```\n\nChrome just refuses to show anything, which made this hard to debug.\n\nWe generate the ca & cert here: https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes/blob/802d214ed0d34a58606991007fdc28823687a424/cluster/saltbase/salt/generate-cert/make-ca-cert.sh#L64\n\nAction items:\n- Every CA we make should be unique, even within the same (e.g.) GCE project/ip address.\n- Every cert we make should have a unique serial number.\n\neasyrsa docs don't make it immediately obvious how to accomplish this.\n",
